The paper introduces a new method for probabilistic graphical models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves caching samples and extracting new sample means, which could be considered a data structure or algorithmic approach (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the method, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper may be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) as it introduces a new approach for sampling in graphical models.
